{%- comment -%} FAQ Page — Azoir {%- endcomment -%}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ 'pages.css' | asset_url }}" media="print" onload="this.media='all'">
<noscript><link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ 'pages.css' | asset_url }}"></noscript>

<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="faq-container">

    <div class="faq-header">
      <span class="faq-eyebrow">FAQ</span>
      <h1 class="faq-title">Common questions</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-groups">

      <div class="faq-group">
        <h2 class="faq-group__title">The commission process</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">How does the commission process work?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>It starts with our commission form — you describe the piece, the occasion, and the person it's for. From there, our jewellers sketch and iterate with you until every detail is right. You approve every stage before we touch metal. Once approved, we handcraft the piece in New York and ship it to you.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">What is the design fee and why is it charged?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>The $59 design fee covers the cost of the initial consultation, sketching, and CAD rendering. It's credited toward your final piece if you proceed. It exists to ensure that both sides are serious before we invest significant design time.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">How many revisions are included?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>We include up to three rounds of revisions in the design phase. In practice, most commissions are finalised in one or two. We don't rush the process — if more iterations are needed to get it right, we'll discuss that with you.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">Can I see a 3D render or wax model before production begins?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>Yes. Depending on the complexity of the piece, we provide CAD renders and, for more intricate commissions, a wax model for your approval before casting.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-group">
        <h2 class="faq-group__title">Timing &amp; pricing</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">How long does a commission take?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>Most commissions are completed within 4–8 weeks from design approval. More complex pieces — those with intricate settings or engraving — may take 10–12 weeks. We'll give you a specific timeline during the design phase.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">What does a bespoke piece cost?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>Pricing depends on the metal, stones, and complexity of the design. Our commissions start at $570 for rings and $590 for pendants. We provide a detailed, itemised quote before any production begins — there are no surprise costs.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">Do you offer payment plans?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>Yes. We offer payment plans for commissions over $1,000. Please mention this when submitting your form and we'll discuss the options with you.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-group">
        <h2 class="faq-group__title">Materials &amp; quality</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">What metals do you work with?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>We work in 18k yellow gold, 18k white gold, 18k rose gold, platinum, and sterling silver. All metals are ethically sourced and, where possible, recycled. We'll recommend the best option for your design during the consultation.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">Are your diamonds and stones conflict-free?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>Yes. We work exclusively with conflict-free stones and can provide full provenance documentation on request. We source from suppliers who comply with the Kimberley Process and, where possible, use lab-grown diamonds as an ethical alternative.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">Is the jewellery hallmarked?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>Yes. All pieces are hallmarked with the metal purity and our maker's mark before delivery.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-group">
        <h2 class="faq-group__title">Shipping &amp; aftercare</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">How is the piece packaged and shipped?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>Every piece ships in Azoir packaging — a matte black box with a cotton-filled interior — via fully insured, tracked courier. We ship internationally. Shipping costs and times will be confirmed at checkout.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">What if I need a resize after receiving the piece?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>We offer one complimentary resize within 60 days of delivery for all ring commissions. After that, resizing is available at a nominal cost. Please contact us and we'll arrange return shipping.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-item__q">Do you offer repairs or maintenance?</summary>
            <div class="faq-item__a">
              <p>Yes. We offer repairs, polishing, and stone replacement for all pieces we've made. Contact us with details of what's needed and we'll provide a quote and arrange collection.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="faq-footer">
      <p class="faq-footer__text">Still have a question?</p>
      <a href="/pages/contact" class="faq-footer__link">Get in touch &rarr;</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<script>
// Native <details> handles open/close — just add close-others behaviour
(function () {
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(function (item) {
    item.addEventListener('toggle', function () {
      if (item.open) {
        document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item[open]').forEach(function (other) {
          if (other !== item) other.removeAttribute('open');
        });
      }
    });
  });
})();
</script>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "FAQ Page",
  "settings": [],
  "presets": [{ "name": "FAQ Page" }]
}
{% endschema %}
